-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/pboc-s-zhou-says-china-s-inflation-starts-to-ease-market-news.html
China ’s central bank governor Zhou
Xiaochuan said that China’s inflation is starting to ease,
Market News International reports.
* Zhou said some of the anti-inflation policies are beginning to
work
* China’s economy may “slowdown a bit” after moderating in the
first and second quarters  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
